100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 8, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva to discuss issues of international security and disarmament amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the trial of the Scopes Monkey case continued to attract national attention, highlighting the clash between modern science and traditional beliefs. Meanwhile, in Russia, the recent death of influential Bolshevik leader Leon Trotsky prompted speculation about the future of the Communist Party under Joseph Stalin's leadership.
